<!doctype html><html>
<head><title>JavaScript Tutorial</title><style type="text/css">#sectiontohide {    padding:20px;    background:#f0f0f0;    width:400px;    display:none;}</style>

<script type="text/javascript">    function toggle_div_fun(id) { 
      var show = document.getElementById(id);       
      if(show.style.display == 'block')  show.style.display = 'none';       
      else   show.style.display = 'block';    }
      </script>
</head>
<body>
  <div onclick="toggle_div_fun('sectiontohide');">Click here</div> 
  to toggle visibility of div element #sectiontohide<br /><br /><div id="sectiontohide"><p>The Remington Chop was a first-time culinary event that took place on June 13th in the Remington neighborhood of Baltimore City. When we started, our mission was to host an event that brought people to a lesser-known neighborhood of Baltimore and give our guests a chance to learn from local chefs. We choose Remington for its burgeoning culinary scene and because of the efforts of the neighborhood to help us put the event together.</p></div>
